,"tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Engage your readers by using second person "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(you, your)"}]},{"type":"text","value":". First person "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"(I, we, our)"}]},{"type":"text","value":" focuses on the writer rather than the audience. People are interested in what they can do and how your story applies to their lives.\nOne exception to this is in the case of possessive adjectives in the UI. You can use first person in headings or labels that are very specific to the user or customer data, for example “My Account” or “My Usage.” In explanatory text for the heading or label, switch to second person, for example "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“Your usage is calculated from the 1st day of the month.”"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"dont-be-too-formal-or-stuffy"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#dont-be-too-formal-or-stuffy","ariaHidden":true,"className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"height":16,"width":16,"fill":"#0062ff","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","viewBox":"0 0 32 32"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"defs","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"style","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".cls-1{fill:none;}"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"title","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"icons"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"g","properties":{"id":"Icon"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M29.2416,6.7587a6.0194,6.0194,0,0,0-8.5039,0l1.4172,1.4171a4.0089,4.0089,0,0,1,5.67,5.6694l-7.9793,7.9791a4.0089,4.0089,0,0,1-5.67-5.6694l1.4176-1.4171L14.176,13.3206l-1.4176,1.4171a6.0131,6.0131,0,0,0,8.5039,8.5036l7.9793-7.9791A6.02,6.02,0,0,0,29.2416,6.7587Z"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M4.1783,24.8217a4.0164,4.0164,0,0,1,0-5.6738l7.9688-7.9672a4.0121,4.0121,0,1,1,5.6746,5.6734l-2.12,2.1195L17.12,20.3918l2.12-2.1195a6.0179,6.0179,0,0,0-8.5114-8.51L2.76,17.73a6.0181,6.0181,0,0,0,8.5114,8.51L9.8529,24.8217A4.0177,4.0177,0,0,1,4.1783,24.8217Z"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"g","properties":{"id":"Transparent_Rectangle","dataName":"Transparent Rectangle"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"rect","properties":{"className":["cls-1"],"x":"-0.0116","y":"-0.0007","width":32,"height":32},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Don't be too formal or stuffy"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Do not be afraid to use contractions once in a while. Decide whether they fit the context."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Occasionally begin sentences with "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"and, but or so."}]},{"type":"text","value":" This usage allows for shorter, scannable sentences. Do not overuse these devices, especially in instructional (steps) content."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For example, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“You can deploy an app to the cloud during lunch hour. And still have time to eat”"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is great for Discover, Try, Buy."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Occasionally use questions in headings. In both UIs and documentation, questions can be used to further conversational style, but don't overuse them, as they can add to noise and hinder retrievability. Make sure headings that use questions are meaningful. In a UI, questions can be used in a confirmation prompt in a dialog box. For example: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“Do you want to close without saving?”"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use exclamation marks only positively, not negatively. Make sure you use no more than one exclamation mark in a context, such as a single window or a single Docs topic."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"flex-group","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"example","properties":{"correct":"true","title":"Exclamation Points","text":"\"Your IBM Bluemix account is ready!\""},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"example","properties":{"title":"Exclamation Points","text":"\"You have reached your usage limit!\""},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"dont-be-overly-mannerly"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#dont-be-overly-mannerly","ariaHidden":true,"className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"height":16,"width":16,"fill":"#0062ff","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","viewBox":"0 0 32 32"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"defs","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"style","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".cls-1{fill:none;}"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"title","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"icons"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"g","properties":{"id":"Icon"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M29.2416,6.7587a6.0194,6.0194,0,0,0-8.5039,0l1.4172,1.4171a4.0089,4.0089,0,0,1,5.67,